data.enText: the practice of obeying rules or requests made by people in authority
procedures that must be followed to ensure full compliance with the law
data.chText: 为确保严格遵守法律所必须遵行的程序

data.enText: Safety measures were carried out in compliance with paragraph 6 of the building regulations.
data.chText: 遵照建筑规程的第6条实施了安全措施。

tr: acting according to certain accepted standards
example: their financial statements are in conformity with generally accepted accounting practices

tr: a disposition or tendency to yield to the will of others

example.ex: Inspectors were sent to visit nuclear sites and verify compliance with the treaty...
example.tran: 监督员被派去视察核武器基地并核实条约的遵守情况。

example.ex: The company says it is in full compliance with US labor laws...
example.tran: 这家公司说自己严格遵守美国的各项劳工法。

example.ex: The Security Council aim to ensure compliance by all sides, once an agreement is signed.
example.tran: 一旦签署协议，安理会的目标就是保证各方都要遵守。

value.def: Compliance with something, for example a law, treaty, or agreement means doing what you are required or expected to do.
